velop","docking,","doesn't","driven","e","earth).","element","envi,","erdas,","esp8266","esri","experienc","fleet","game","geograph","geographi","geomatica","gitbook","github","graticul","graticule,","hard","hat","he'","http,","https://ablakey.github.io/periodic/index.html","https://ablakey.github.io/st","https://github.com/ablakey/leaflet.simplegraticul","https://github.com/ablakey/minibu","https://github.com/locusrobotics/qgis_ro","implementation,","indoor","industri","info","interfac","javascript","land/wat","lead","leaflet","led","let'","link","links,","local","machin","machine/index.html","mail:","manag","mani","map","mapping,","master'","mayb","messag","minibu","mobil","mobile.","modbu","monitor","name","names!","on","once.","opc","oper","overview","part","peer","perform","period","pick","plc","process","project","projects,","python","qgi","qgis,","qgis.","queuing,","real","reference.","repositori","ro","robot","robot,","roboticist","ros,","run","safeti","scheduling,","server","server,","servic","set","simpl","site","socket","softwar","space","stack:","state","survey","system","tabl","task","team","testing,","they'r","thing","time","too!","topic","tri","typescript","u.s.","ua","ui/ux","unfortun","univers","unproject","us","visit","water","waterloo.","wearer","web","webrtc,","websocket,","well","with:","within","work","zeromq)"],"pipeline":["stopWordFilter","stemmer"]},"store":{"./":{"url":"./","title":"Overview","keywords":"","body":"Overview\nThis GitBook is a collection of assorted projects, links, and info assembled by Andrew Blakey.\nFor the most part the contents are for my own reference. But maybe they're useful for you too!\n"},"projects.html":{"url":"projects.html","title":"Projects","summary":"Things I've put together over the years. A lot of them are for fun, some were for work or academics.","keywords":"","body":"Projects\nQGIS-ROS\nA set of adapters to access ROS topics from within QGIS.\nhttps://github.com/locusrobotics/qgis_ros\nThe State Machine\nA game where you try to visit every U.S. state once.\nhttps://ablakey.github.io/state-machine/index.html\nMinibus\nA Modbus server running on an ESP8266\nhttps://github.com/ablakey/minibus\nLeaflet Simple Graticule\nA graticule, but for unprojected Cartesian spaces (flat Earth).\nhttps://github.com/ablakey/Leaflet.SimpleGraticule\nPeriodic Table of GitHub\nBecause naming repositories is hard so let's pick element names!\nUnfortunately this one doesn't work too well on mobile.\nhttps://ablakey.github.io/periodic/index.html\n"},"links.html":{"url":"links.html","title":"Links","keywords":"","body":"Links\n"},"about.html":{"url":"about.html","title":"About","keywords":"","body":"About\nAndrew Blakey is a software developer who has been working in the industrial mobile robotics industry since 2013. Before that he completed a Bachelor's and Master's in Geography at the University of Waterloo.\nHe is a:\n\nRoboticist-Geographer\nExperienced team lead\nWearer of many hats\n\nHe works with:\n\nROS - the Robot Operating System\nPython\nTypeScript / JavaScript\nC#\nQGIS, ESRI Arc-All-The-Things\nENVI, ERDAS, Geomatica\n\nHe's led projects on all parts of the stack:\n\nWeb / mobile applications\nUI/UX design, application architecture, implementation, testing, deployment\nRobot mapping, configuration, task scheduling, monitoring\nFleet management and monitoring\n\n\nWeb servers and databases\nCloud, local server, on-robot\nReal-time message-driven services and database APIs\nRobot, site mapping, land/water surveying\n\n\nReal-time robot fleet management \nCentralized and peer-to-peer\nTask allocation, queuing, docking, scheduling, safety behaviors\n\n\nIndustrial interfaces\nRobot -> PLC communications\nFleet Management -> Modbus and OPC-UA\n\n\nRobot communications\nROS, HTTP, WebSocket, WebRTC, Sockets (eg. ZeroMQ)\n\n\nData processing\nRobotic water surveying\nIndoor mobile robot mapping performance\n\n\n\nE-Mail: ablakey@gmail.com\n"}}}